      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Assume that acetyl CoA containing a <sup>14</sup>C isotopic label in the carboxyl carbon atom is used as starting material and that the mevalonate pathway is followed. Identify the positions in <i>α</i>-cadinol where the label would appear.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBczRiIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--f522ba9749558eabb84f75fa68ecb6a5b8ee2edf/OChem_27_EC_010.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of alpha-cardinol. It comprises of a trans-decalin ring with an endo double bond, exo-substituted hydroxyl, isopropyl, and two methyl groups.\">",
